My utmost professional tool review of the @flexpowertoolsna barrel grip jigsaw. (D handles are for children)
Ask them, but I heard, they’re coming out with some bigger tools soon.

Emily and I got to show off our @badgertoolbelts at her day school today. We had the kids use hammers and nails and put the last of the screws into each house and hammer in the perch for the birds. Emily led the building project. 
.
.
To say I’m grateful for the life I have is an understatement.

#Plumbers and #hvac people. Is it worth it for me to #mastic all the joints of the ducting in my basement? 
If so which mastic do you prefer? 
Thanks!
null

I’ll just leave this right here. 
.
.
.
Thank you to my wife @angelagosselink for always supporting me. My daughter, parents, family and friends for asking and helping me get through this. We started this before Covid and it has been a burden just not knowing and not being to get any answers from anyone.
I wish I was better with words.

This is a foot activated biscuit joiner. First time I ever saw one @greene_st_joinery just put it up in a group I’m in with him. 
Why isn’t this still a thing? If you got the hold down on an actuator that went with the foot activation it would be incredible. And this would work really well with a @festoolsedge @festoolcanada domino. 
I know this wouldn’t replace a handheld joiner but it could definitely speed up a lot of processes. 
It’s the @deltamachinery 32-100 plate joiner. Sounds like they stopped making it in the 80’s 
I feel like I’d use this all the time on site.

Cold weather setting for @stihlcanada br600 and above, also chainsaws. It’s like a brand new blower. For use only when it’s really really cold. Supposedly it redirects the exhaust to the carb so it stays warm and works better. 
Well it for sure works better!!!!
Just make sure to turn off t back in the summer or you’ll overheat your engine. 
Maybe I should start reading user manuals lol

That’s an 8’6” X 11’ triple lane sliding door. 

There’s a ton to learn at the new job. I’d like to thank  @battersbyhowat and @signalconstruction, david especially as he is who hired me, for entrusting me with my position. And Amanda our site manager. 
This may be and I think is, the most organized job site I’ve ever been on. 
I have a new role as project lead, I deal mainly with subs and more of the day to day on the job. It’s quite the job site. Probably the most technically difficult I’ve ever been on. 
As I get further and further into my position I’ll start posting more. I’ll have some carpentry stuff with a lot of the details of the job. 
I hope you follow, this is going to be downright amazing when it’s done.

. I think I may start a series on figuring out layout for milkwork and what goes into finding where everything goes. Between the specialty lighting, different ceiling types, barrisol ceiling, hvac plenums, reveals, no casings on the doors, nor jambs, inset drapery tracks and don’t even get me started on the sound diffusion and absorption in the theatre it’s a lot of info to get the measurements for one room.
But it’s getting better  everyday and I’d rather have a challenge!

13 years today. This is one of the many reasons that make getting sober worth it. 
I still have my struggles, life isn’t perfect but it’s good, damn good. 
I just wanted to say thank you to @angelagosselink, Emily, my parents and family, and all the people who have helped support me and my sobriety. 
#sober #sobriety #amianoldtimeryet

I don’t know how long this will stay up. 

I had it easy when I got sober. I had had a normal childhood with loving parents, a good family, friends, I grew up in a good neighborhood, got a good education. Not everyone has that. I don’t feel like my path to sobriety was easy. But I know many people have it a lot harder than me. They don’t have support, they grew up in fucked up families, they don’t have friends that support their decision. They have everything going against them. 
Very few people get and stay sober, I hope I can stay sober until I die. Now I’m just rambling. 
Just
 think about people who are out there on the streets drinking and using, selling their souls. It’s not fun, it’s not a blast, its fucking terrible. it saddens me, it’s disheartening, I want to help each and every one see the other side but I can’t and they can’t see it themselves. 
That could have been me. At the rate I was going it wasn’t to far off. But I had the help and support of everyone around me. I was damn lucky.
Excited for my next one!! Couldn’t be two better pouch companies together! @badgertoolbelts @occidentalleather.toolbelts
Thanks for the audio @benbogie It made it a lot faster making this remix lol.

What do you hold your measurements to? It was a question recently asked in a FB group I’m in. This piece of flooring that transitions directly into tile had a 3/32” bow in it which would have made a lip to the tile. So we fixed it. Would you have why or why not?
Also, I’ve had this @solameasuringtools 4’ level for 6 or 7 years and it’s still dead accurate.

One of my favorite #decks I’ve ever built and definitely one I wish I could go back and see again. 
It also helps when they’re some of the best clients you’ve ever had.
6 years ago today.

The amount of work in these two pics is mind boggling. Double stud wall with 3/8” sound isolation between the ceiling and floor, Rockwool, sound isolation clips and hat track, 3/4” ply, 5/8” Sheetrock. All holes filled with foam backer rod and @sika_canada, flush base, speaker boxes at certain heights and points in the room, ladder trusses for the drop ceiling spaced to not hit the speaker boxes and be close to 48” on center and in the form of a W . The Sheetrock packed out 2 1/4” but spaces to fit C channel metal of different widths. Then sheath all the walls again with 1/2” ply except where the 22 channels will go, and finally 1 1/8” fabric to cover everything. theres more, lots more. To much. 1,000’s of hours for one room. Most of it behind the scenes. That’s what we do when we are sitting behind the desk. 
Sorry if I missed anything Scott Justin and Amanda. Lol

Our tile guy is immaculate, I’ve only worked with one other one that had his skill.
He had a giant that worked for him and a guy named Red who looked like he was stuck in an 80’s hair band  and blew up himself with a grenade in Belleville NJ.
Off that diatribe Roger is damn good and not having to worry about him or his work  makes life as a white hardhatter incredible! 
Oh and that’s a true story he blew himself up with a grenade. 
And these tiles are 4X10. There’s 2 of them they do the whole ceiling and miter up into the window wells.

It’s a big W on the ceiling. It takes a team to build homes like this is the number one thing I’m finding out in my new role @signalconstruction 
If you just have to go in and build to the CAD drawings that someone gave you. Know that there could be hundreds of hours that went into that and now you’re gin man build it in a lot less hours. 
From theatre to designers to architects to electricians and hvac engineers and sound engineers. And the list just goes on.

I’ve been using this @truewerk pouch since I started at @signalconstruction about four months ago. It’s been a lifesaver. It will not replace a full belt setup but for what I do it’s perfect. Slides in and out of the pouch easy and is held tight by the hook and loop pocket. 
If you’re more in a #whitehardhat role this might be the pouch for you!
And how did you figure it???

One of my first posts on IG was building a lemonade stand for my nieces. 3 pallets and 3 hours later Emily has a one of a kind lemonade stand. To say I’m grateful for Emily and @angelagosselink is an understatement. It puts a lump in my throat just thinking about the two of them. 
Off to princess auto later to pick up a dolly and rip the casters off. 
#soberalcoholic
I thought the elevator guys would need a lot more stuff than this to install the elevator. It will be in and running by Friday.

Help! After many years of pure abuse my @igaging square is done. Is a @starrett_tools or any other high end square worth it in real life abuse, it will be used as a chisel and scraper sometimes.
The price of these igaging squares has tripled since I bought them from $11 to $33, $26 if I get it at busy bee but it will take me half an hour and probably $7 in gas to get there. 
I’m not to keen on buying nice stuff I know will be abused.
Just a big ole photo dump of some of the work that’s been going on @signalconstruction site that I wear my white hard hat to.

Using thousands of the @knappconnectors klick connectors on this #hemlock ceiling. Not one exposed fastener on the ceiling. If you go to pic 2 and 3 you can see how they work. The cloth is there so for the 1/2” reveals you won’t see the framing.
Brought to you by @signalconstruction

Framing for the wood burning fireplace almost finished up. You can see in the second pic @wizzerj thought up these “knife plates” to support the bench area. The bench will receive 3/4” stone, the fireplace will get stone, metal panels, plaster, custom plate steel wood and kindling storage, custom fireplace tools and hanger along with hidden stocking hangers. 
@signalconstruction

July 31 2020 I sliced my @truewerk pants with a razor knife. I asked them if there was something to fix them and they told me of some stuff. I never fixed them and the whole hasn’t grown since. Great work #truewerk

I got to wear my belt for a little while squaring up and straightening this wall. 
And there’s a pic of some hanging paper balls that will be hanging @bocci balls. 
Maybe they’ll repost the final pic when the hanging balls are up?

I need help from my North American followers. I need a lead on these deck pedestals. They’re for leveling out a flat roof to accept either framing or the panel systems. 
Our supplier @windsorplywood.shpk has been trying to find them without getting much back. There’s a few companies that make them. 
If you know of anyone that can help us out getting in touch with the manufacturer of these pedestals it will be appreciated. 
This one is made by Ryno
Our big girl turned 5 yesterday. Shes just an incredible kid. Kind heart, smart, funny and an infectious laugh!
Just a mock up but man that wasn’t fun. And now there’s I think more than ten left to do in the finished floor. But hey I’d do this anyway over cookie cutter charge by ft ² flat stock.

I forget just how fucking cool this job was. 
Everything except for the columns was built on a bench (at a gentleman’s height) on the ground and then lifted into place.
All sapele mahogany, much of the trim made and assembled on site in winter. The egg and dart type moulding was all separate pieces individually placed on. 
Oh and the doors were existing so that made it a little more complicated. 
And finally no this was not designed or built  by one of the real housewives of New Jerseys husband even though he takes credit for it.

There’s tradespeople that you meet that show the utmost professionalism. @iron_elements_inc is one of them. 
Bruce and his team are just some of the most competent, easiest going, and I just trust them. If there is a problem they’re going to tell me and already have a solution in hand and then dove right in. 
If you’re looking for decorative metal work in Edmonton please get in touch with them. 
Oh and this is a firewood storage bin. Kindling on the bottom and logs on top. 
Thank you for the drawings also @wizzerj @signalconstruction

Daddy @badgertoolbelts , mommy #badgertoolbelt and Emily #badgertoolbelts 
All custom all one of a kind. 
Joel you hit it out of the park with @angelagosselink #toolbelt!! 
Thank you for getting it in time for her birthday! 
Angela’s is a custom right handed belt with a few extras added in. And if you didn’t know she is a red seal certified carpenter. Which is pretty kick ass. She doesn’t work as a carpenter anymore but she’s still in the construction field! 
Joel, I appreciate all the support and the friendship through the years and I still kick myself for not stopping by to meet you when I moved up here from jersey. 
Love you Ang and I hope you get decades of use out of your belt!

So I guess I haven’t showed this enough. If you need to get caulking or spray foam in hard to reach spaces use a piece of romex taped to it. Leave the bare wire in so you can flex it and keep it in position. if you make the wire long enough you can use the gun upside down and be applying  the spray foam above the gun. Also helps to get into hard to reach places.

I feel quite odd modeling my new @badgertoolbelts.
Completely custom belt for the white hard hats that sometimes swing a hammer. 
No hammer sleeve but in intergrated hammer ring. Knife spot with the no cut fabric for my solid knife. At least 29 spots to put my mark by tools. 
Right side pouch is a pretty normal pouch except for the perfectly placed American and Canadian flag. 
iPad holder that comes off easily and extra fastener pouch. 
I was able to wear it today and it will not be leaving me. It’s also really comfortable to wear while sitting in a chair making emails. 
I truly can’t tell you enough if you’re looking for a new belt please look at Joel and #badgertoolbelt. 
He’s incredible to work with, an absolutely great human being and my belt completely exceeded my expectations!!
#toolbelt #toolbelts @badgertoolbelts.korea 
I’ll go through the belt more in my stories over the next few days.

I need your help because these look like a dogs bollocks. I need exterior heaters that will have a gas line fed directly to them no tank. Not really looking for overhead heaters either. Something that looks good and works good.
Thank you. 
We already have a wood and gas fireplace outside, this is secondary.

A circle is a square and sometimes a triangle. Two framing squares make it easy to find the diameter of a circle. 
Just a simple trick
Once you find the diameter you can find the radius and then use the square to make your circle.
